[quote=&quot;Tr0n&quot;:9wl8zr9n]playerid is a build-in quest numeric.[/quote:9wl8zr9n]
I know, but where Elex put [b:9wl8zr9n]use knife on #player#[/b:9wl8zr9n], whatever is entered in place of #player# is just entered into the [i:9wl8zr9n]player[/i:9wl8zr9n] string variable.  What to do after that?

I thought it would be [b:9wl8zr9n]#@player#[/b:9wl8zr9n].  Then you would put something like...

[code:9wl8zr9n]set numeric &lt;id; $id&#40;#player#&#41;$&gt;
set numeric &lt;health&#91;id&#93;; %health&#91;id&#93;% - $rand&#40;12; 40&#41;$&gt;
msgto &lt;%id%; |b$name&#40;%userid%&#41;$|xb attacked you, causing damage!&gt;
msg &lt;You attacked $name&#40;%id%&#41;$&gt;[/code:9wl8zr9n]

Not tested properly, I looked into [i:9wl8zr9n]arena.asl[/i:9wl8zr9n] to see how player interaction worked, I'm guessing a basic attacking function would work based on these methods.
